- Network protocols define a set of rules/standards for data communication over a network  <marks>1 mark</marks>
- TCP/IP is a suite of protocols that enables communication between different devices/networks <marks>1 mark</marks>

$$
\begin{align*}
&\text{TCP (Transmission Control Protocol):} \\
&\quad\bullet\; \text{Ensures reliable data transfer} \\
&\quad\bullet\; \text{Handles flow control, error checking, and retransmission}
\end{align*}
$$

$$
\begin{align*}
&\text{IP (Internet Protocol):}\\
&\quad\bullet\; \text{Handles logical addressing and routing of data packets}\\
&\quad\bullet\; \text{Allows communication across different networks}
\end{align*}
$$

<marks>1 mark</marks> for explaining the role of TCP
<marks>1 mark</marks> for explaining the role of IP
